T is the so-called orthogonal matrix, and it contains eigenvec-
tors corresponding to eigenvalues.
 Step 3: Select k principal components. If the sum of eigenvalues
ratio reaches a certain level, such as 85 percent, k is the number
of the principal. Then these k components can replace all the
independent variables, and calculate the score matrix Zk.

