The article collected data (cite: Chinese Statistical Yearbook) from 1999 to 2009 in Jiangxi province and its inﬂuencing factors in rail freight. Speciﬁc data will be shown in Table 1.
Assuming GDP, total retail sales of social consumer goods, primary sector, secondary industry, tertiary-industry, total export-import volume, denoted as X ¼ ½x1 … x6. And railway rotation volume of freight transport is expressed as Y. These data can be found in Table 1. And the ﬁrst ﬁve data is one hundred million RMB for the unit, the last data uses one hundred million tons as one unit. Then, the autocorrelation coefﬁcients of the variables can be calculated through using the data set in Table 1. Speciﬁc data can be expressed in Table 2. According to Table 2, the autocorrelation coefﬁcients of the variables is large. Then the problem that independent variable existing severe multiple correlations has been seen.

