2.4. Modiﬁed partial least squares regression (MPLSR)

PCR and PLSR will project the raw data into the principal component space, latent variable space and free space. And the multicollinearity problem that is a obstacle for the OLSR. Through the lower dimension of principal components space or latent variables space, this problem can be overcame. But, these methods will have any deviation on the result of PCR and PLSR. When the set data exists multicollinearity problem or the number of samples less than the number of variables, OLSR can't work very well. In order to solve these problems, Yin et al. proposed the MPLSR, which has been veriﬁed on the industrial benchmark of Tennessee Eastman process for fault detection [29] and a good result has been obtained [30]. MPLSR can avoid these drawbacks and it can provide a clearer interpretation of the correlation model. MPLSR has less computational load than the other three algorithms. And the algorithm can be expressed speciﬁcally as follows.

 Step 1: Place collected variables into X and Y. Normalize them,



represented as X ¼ ½x1 … xm A RnÂm and Y ¼ ½y1 … yp A RnÂp. Step 2: Calculate eigenvalues and eigenvectors of XT X.

