in which yi is the observed value for the i-th sample; y^ ip is the model predicted response values for the i-th sample, respectively; n is the number of observed samples.
The cumulative percent variance select 95 percent as standard. It will be ﬁrstly applied to select the number of PCs. PLSR can also select its main inﬂuence component. But for MPLSR, it is not necessary to select the main indexes. Fig. 1 shows the predicting efﬁciency of different models obtained by PCR, PLSR and MPLSR. As it is shown in Fig. 1, three simulation results can describe the relationship between the actual value and the predicted value in PCR, PLSR and MPLSR. The diagonal line in the ﬁgure represents the ideal situation that actual values are the same as the predicted values exactly. However, three prediction models will produce certain error. If the point is more closer to the diagonal, the difference between the predicted values and actual values is more smaller. Then it explains that prediction has a better effect. From three simulation results, MPLSR has the smallest difference between the predicted values and actual values. Therefore, the predicted values are closest to the actual values than other methods. Then, the best prediction can be obtained. In MPLSR model, there exists very little difference between the predicted values and actual values. The RMS values denote the predicted ability of different models. Then Table 3 can also show that the predicting efﬁciency of MPLSR is the best among these three models while PCR model is the worst through the RMS values.

In accordance with Fig. 1 and Table 3, it is obvious that disparate multivariate statistical methods will signally inﬂuence the result of the prediction model. Because of multicollinearity problem and the number of samples less than that of variables in the data set, the OLSR is thoroughly impracticable for constructing the prediction model. Through comparing the values of RMS, the phenomenon that MPLSR has good predictive ability can be discovered. So, in the paper, the railway freight volume of Jiangxi province will be predicted by MPLSR in the next ﬁve years.

3.3. Railway logistics forecast of Jiangxi province in next ﬁve years

Through the above analysis, the error of building model with MPLSR is minimal. Then in this section the data will be forecasted by MPLSR. Before predicting the data of next ﬁve years, some main affecting indexes should be selected by comparing the contribution. In order to analyze the contribution of the railway logistics forecast's every affecting index, a contribution ratio (CR) is introduced and it can be formulated as follows:

y À P0 ¼ PX;

CRi

¼

Pixi yÀP0

P ¼ ½P1; P2…Pm A R1Âm

X ¼ ½x1; x2…xmT A R1Âm

i ¼ 1; …; m

ð25Þ

where P is the coefﬁcient matrix of regression equation and P0 is the constant. The beneﬁts of this deﬁnition for CR are that the sum of all CRi ði ¼ 1⋯mÞ equals 1.
To simplify the model or get rid of the unproﬁtable indexes which contribute little to the predicted values, the CR threshold is applied. And the otiose indexes will be ignored if its CR is lower than the CR threshold. As the best prediction model, MPLSR model is applied to analyze the CR of each index and selects main affecting indexes. The contribution rate of six factors inﬂuencing the railway freight volume in Jiangxi province can be obtained by MATLAB programs, and it will be shown in Fig. 2. As can be seen from the ﬁgure, these three indexes, i.e. GDP, total retail sales of consumer goods, secondary industry, play major roles among the six factors. And their cumulative contribution value has reached 0.95. Therefore, the three factors meet the predicted needs. And the new model based on the selected factors still presents a good railway freight volume predicting ability by MPLSR method.
Using raw data in Table 1, the data of these three factors is presented. And then the equation will be predicted by MPLSR as follows:

y ¼ 497:1442 þ 0:1016x^ 1 À 0:4590x^ 2 þ 0:1344x^ 3

ð26Þ

where x^ 1, x^ 2 and x^ 3 represents the factors after completing screening.
According to the twelfth ﬁve year plan targets of Jiangxi province in China, GDP growth rate will reach 11 percent. The total retail sales of social consumer goods will manage to achieve 16 percent while secondary industry will attain 23 percent. With the growth rate of these three factors, the value of 2010 can be determined. By calculation, railway logistics of Jiangxi province in 2010 is 685.5 billion tonne-km. And the growth of railway logistics in next ﬁve years may reach at 4 percent. Then it will be used to predict railway logistics from 2011 to 2015. And the speciﬁc data can be seen in Table 4.

4. Conclusion
